182
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,450
但现在是时候了
But it's time.

183
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,660
你会成为一个伟大的总统的
You'll make a great president.

184
00:10:35,660 --> 00:10:36,370
我们会确保的
We'll see to that.

185
00:10:36,370 --> 00:10:39,130
等等  我们把话说明白
Now, wait, wait. Let's be clear, okay?

186
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:42,860
我知道我们一直在狠狠打压她
I know we've been hitting her pretty hard,

187
00:10:42,860 --> 00:10:45,560
但我不能允许再对她下一次手
but I can't condone another attempt.

188
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,050
-我做不到  -冷静
- I can't. - Calm down.

189
00:10:47,430 --> 00:10:49,210
天啊  马克  说真的
My God, Mark. I mean, really.

190
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:50,940
还有其他办法
There are other ways.

191
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,820
好  我们是要弹劾她
Okay, so we're talking about impeachment

192
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,480
还是国会政府
or a congressional government?

193
00:10:55,490 --> 00:10:58,360
第25修正案第四款
25th Amendment, Section 4.

194
00:10:59,810 --> 00:11:01,340
从来没人用过
Which has never been used.

195
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:05,320
是为了迅速扼杀信心危机
It's built for speed, intended to smother a crisis of confidence.

196
00:11:05,690 --> 00:11:07,000
让民众安心
Reassure the public.

197
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,760
让世界安心
Reassure the world

198
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,240
美国政府还能继续运作
that continuity remains at the American government,

199
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,030
就算总统变得...
even if a president becomes...

200
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:16,900
-无法履行他的职责  -她的职责
- Unable to fulfill his duties. - Her duties.

201
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,370
-前提是她无法胜任  -她现在确实无法胜任
- It requires her to be unfit. - And she is.

202
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:22,440
而且
I mean...

203
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:25,220
我们的律师已经查过了
our lawyers have already looked into this.

204
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:27,210
她只要能力不足就行
She only needs to be deficient.

205
00:11:27,410 --> 00:11:30,800
法律写得模棱两可  可以变通
The language is vague and accommodating.

206
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:34,630
马克  如果你对此
Mark, if you have any doubt about this

207
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,190
-有所顾虑  -继续说
- at all-- - I'm just listening.

208
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,800
内阁听命于你
The Cabinet is yours.

209
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:45,500
你在参众两院都有关系
You have relationships inside the Senate, the House,

210
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:47,490
两党也都有人脉
on both sides of the aisle.

211
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,130
非常合适
It's a natural fit.

212
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:52,430
但这事必须做得
But the thing has to cascade with--

213
00:11:52,430 --> 00:11:53,470
天衣无缝
Precision.

214
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:57,130
先由副总统和内阁多数成员
A chain reaction beginning with a letter to Congress,

215
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,300
联名写信给国会
signed by the vice president

216
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,060
建议弹劾我
and a majority of his Cabinet,

217
00:12:03,070 --> 00:12:05,230
然后形成连锁反应
recommending my removal from office.

218
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:08,540
我怎么会猜到他们的招数
And how do I know that's what they'll try to do?

219
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:12,500
因为第25条就是冲我来的
Because the 25th gets personal.

220
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:16,000
比尔喜欢我做落难少女
Bill likes me being the damsel in distress.

221
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,880
想得美吧
He wishes I were.

222
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:26,330
你去哪儿
Where you headed?

223
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:28,590
我在北方有家人
I have family up north.

224
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:29,780
哪儿
Where?

225
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:31,280
北方
North.

226
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,150
凯茜的姐姐还在科德角吗
Cathy's sister still on the Cape?

227
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:37,760
在海恩尼斯  是吧
Hyannis, right?

228
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:40,860
很好
It's good.

229
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,460
家人很重要
Family's important.

230
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:44,150
尤其是在艰难时刻
Especially during trying times--

231
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:45,680
我也想请你进来  但我真的...
I'd invite you in, but I really--

232
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:47,840
有些事我总想不通
There's still something that I can't get straight.

233
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,970
你再跟我说一遍吧  当时
If we could go through it one more time. So...

234
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,820
她被一辆车接去医生那儿
She was picked up by car to be taken to the doctor.

235
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:53,460
她不太舒服
She wasn't feeling well.

236
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:55,770
直到她发生栓塞前你一直跟她在一起
You were with her the whole time leading up to the embolism?

237
00:12:55,770 --> 00:12:57,470
斯坦普先生  够了
Mr. Stamper, enough!

238
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:59,710
我只想弄清怎么回事
I'm just trying to understand what happened.

239
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:04,180
你别再来缠着我了
I don't need you coming around here anymore.

240
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,020
你清楚是怎么一回事
You know exactly what happened.

241
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:08,820
也知道验尸结果  事情就是这样
You have the coroner's conclusions. And that's that.

242
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:16,320
我还在哀悼我妻子
I'm in mourning for my wife,

243
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:19,700
我不想再提起她生命的最后时刻
and I'm not reliving the final moments of her life anymore.

244
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:20,660
不想跟你提
Not with you.

245
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:23,490
我觉得你妻子是被谋杀的
I think your wife was murdered.

246
00:13:28,670 --> 00:13:30,020
我要关门了
I'm closing the door now.

247
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:55,560
-喂  -道格  我是弗莱德·安博格
- Hello. - Doug. Fred Amburg here.

248
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,870
-这是谁的电话  -我的
- Whose phone is this? - This one's mine.

249
00:13:59,930 --> 00:14:01,040
我刚出来
I just got out.

250
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:02,240
我才知道
I had no idea.

251
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:04,060
我今早还跟科尔通过话
I talked to Cole this morning.

252
00:14:04,330 --> 00:14:07,320
我听说了件我们那位心理医生的事
Heard an interesting thing about our esteemed shrink.

253
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:09,570
他休假了  事假
You know, that sabbatical, leave,

254
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:11,330
去旅行了  随你怎么说
walkabout, whatever you want to call it.

255
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:13,780
你在找他  是吧
You are looking for him, aren't you?

256
00:14:14,070 --> 00:14:15,020
对
Yes.

257
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,750
他在弗吉尼亚州的一间小屋
He's in a cabin down in Virginia.

258
00:14:40,430 --> 00:14:41,340
给
Here you go.

259
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:49,830
我可以...
Would you mind if I...?

260
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,440
谢谢
Thanks.

261
00:15:09,330 --> 00:15:10,600
喂
Oh, hello?

262
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:14,110
别说话  别开口  等着
Don't say another word. Don't speak. Just wait.

263
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:41,590
抱歉  我拐错弯  跑进楼梯井了
My apologies, I took a wrong turn and wound up in some stairwell.

264
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,180
我们时间不多  得赶回楼上
We don't have much time until we have to get back upstairs.

265
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,990
玛茜最初跟我提这个想法时
When Marcy first came to me with this proposition,

266
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:54,190
豪不夸张地说  我震惊了
I was stunned, to say the least.

267
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:56,530
直到近来
Until recently I--

268
00:15:56,810 --> 00:15:59,920
我才...我没想到事情会这么糟
I don't know. I didn't realize how truly bad things were.

269
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:03,270
但赶总统下台  我的天啊
But unseat the president? Jesus Christ.

270
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,420
总统是我的朋友
President's my friend.

271
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:12,160
虽说我担心她的精神状况
And while I worry about her mental state,

272
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,640
但我更担心国家的状况
I worry about the state of this nation more.

273
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:18,230
副总统先生  我很敬佩你
Mr. Vice President, I admire you greatly.

274
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:20,570
但我不习惯做这种事
But I'm not used to this kind of thing.

275
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:22,530
背地里谋算
Back rooms, after hours.

276
00:16:22,530 --> 00:16:24,240
我们得一万个小心
We need to take every precaution.

277
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:26,980
光是过来就很危险了
And yet we're still at risk just by being here.

278
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,170
抱歉
I'm sorry,

279
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:31,090
但我相信总统一职的神圣性
but I believe in the sanctity of the office of the presidency.

280
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,740
所以我们才聚在这里
And that's exactly why we're here.

281
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:35,000
你这是让我们背弃誓言
You're asking us to betray an oath.

282
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,740
我是让大家吐露心声
I'm asking you to speak your mind.

283
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:39,760
这里的每个人齐心协力
A concentrated effort, all of us in this room.

284
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:42,260
我们或许救不了总统
We may not be able to save the president,

285
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:44,810
但或许救得了我们的政府
but we may just be able to save our administration.

286
00:16:44,810 --> 00:16:47,620
第25条不仅要看准时机
The 25th is not just about timing.

287
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:49,570
还要绝对保密
It's about secrecy.

288
00:16:49,820 --> 00:16:51,560
参议院一向守不住秘密
And the Senate hasn't kept a secret--

289
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:52,650
厄尔  感谢你提到这一点
Earl, I appreciate that.

290
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:55,230
众议院已在我掌控之中  参议院也交给我
I have the House, and I'll take care of the Senate.

291
00:16:55,230 --> 00:16:56,470
我会起草一封信
I'll prepare a letter

292
00:16:56,470 --> 00:16:58,860
详细列出总统的渎职
detailing the president's dereliction of duty,

293
00:16:58,860 --> 00:17:01,750
向国会和后世解释清楚
laying out a case for Congress and for posterity.

294
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,400
等时机成熟  就会通知大家
And when the time comes, you'll all be notified.

295
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,890
我们都是爱国者
Look, we're all patriots here.

296
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:11,790
我们最牵挂的  我们唯一牵挂的  必须是
Our first concern, our only concern, has got to be...

297
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,450
国家的生死存亡
the survival of our nation.

298
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,790
该死
Fuck!

299
00:18:21,020 --> 00:18:22,730
坐下吧  深呼吸
Sit and take a deep breath.

300
00:18:25,940 --> 00:18:26,880
坐下
Sit down.

301
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:32,810
罗森医生  坐下
Dr. Rosen, sit down.

302
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:46,340
你怎么进来的
How did you get in here?

303
00:18:52,470 --> 00:18:54,660
我想  你在这儿是因为你很痛苦
I'm assuming you're here because you're suffering.

304
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:58,520
如果不是为佐伊·巴恩斯
And if it's not over Zoe Barnes,

305
00:18:59,050 --> 00:19:02,490
就是为另一个被你毁掉的人
it's over some other soul that you've torn apart.

306
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:03,450
不对
No.

307
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:05,120
你想  我在这儿
You're assuming I'm here

308
00:19:05,130 --> 00:19:07,370
是因为我发现了你拿走了我什么东西
because I figured out what you took from me.

309
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:10,900
-拿走  -没给我
- Took? - Kept.

310
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:19,190
所有个人物品都应该在出院时归还原主
All personal property should have been returned upon release.

311
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:21,550
你说得对  是应该
You're right. It should have.

312
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:25,650
专业人士竟然做出这种事
There's no accounting for the behavior of supposed professionals.

313
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:34,030
我曾经在社交场合遇到过一个心理医生
I once met this psychologist, socially,

314
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:34,980
她跟我说
who told me about

315
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:37,650
她曾经给同僚们办了一次派对
a party that she hosted once for a group of her peers.

316
00:19:37,650 --> 00:19:39,580
请了一屋子的心理医生
It was just a roomful of shrinks.

317
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:41,950
那晚派对结束后  她在打扫
At the end of the night, she was cleaning up,

318
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:43,750
走进卫生间
she went into the bathroom

319
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:47,040
发现她的某个同事把屎
and she saw that one of her colleagues had smeared shit

320
00:19:47,570 --> 00:19:49,280
糊了一墙
all over the bathroom wall.

321
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:52,790
什么变态会做出那种事
Now, what kind of fucked up person would do something like that?

322
00:19:55,620 --> 00:19:58,540
看来传言是真的
Well, I guess it's true what they say.

323
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,570
心理医生才是最变态的
That shrinks are the most fucked up of all.

324
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:06,250
那种行为很是暴力
Such a violence to that act.

325
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:10,640
但暴力很有趣
But violence is a funny thing.

326
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,690
其实受害者记得最清楚的
You know, it's not so much the physical pain

327
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:16,390
不是肉体上的疼痛
that can victims can remember.

328
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,120
而是当时的感觉
It's the feelings around it.

329
00:20:20,330 --> 00:20:21,360
那种恐惧
The fear.

330
00:20:24,930 --> 00:20:27,110
在哪  你扣下的遗嘱在哪  你放哪了
Where is it? The will you intercepted? Where is it?

331
00:20:27,110 --> 00:20:29,010
已经不在我这儿了
I don't have it anymore.

332
00:20:32,590 --> 00:20:33,880
不在我这儿
I don't have it!

333
00:20:36,740 --> 00:20:37,860
里面写了什么
What was in it?

334
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:44,290
他把一切都留给了你
He left you everything.

335
00:21:02,420 --> 00:21:03,440
天啊
God...

336
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:09,020
拿着吧
Take it.

337
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:12,150
谢谢
Thank you.

338
00:21:15,980 --> 00:21:17,640
我当时就觉得那么问很奇怪
I thought it was a strange question.

339
00:21:19,630 --> 00:21:20,570
什么
What?

340
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:23,400
你问我弗兰西斯·安德伍德留给我什么了
When you asked me what Francis Underwood had given me.

341
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,550
遗嘱的结语就是这样的
That's how the will ends.

342
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:30,880
"记住我最后给你的那样东西"
"Remember the last thing I gave you."

343
00:21:38,850 --> 00:21:41,850
别给她打电话  否则我会回来的
Don't call her or I'll be back.

344
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,440
希望你能搞清楚自己的问题  医生
Hope you figure out your problems, Doctor.

345
00:22:17,810 --> 00:22:18,770
拿走吧
Take it.

346
00:22:20,290 --> 00:22:21,890
想要的话  就送你了
If you want it, it's yours.

347
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:29,810
你想没想过  自己过的是别人的生活
Do you ever wonder if you're living somebody else's life?

348
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:31,920
你过的是谁的生活  简
Whose life are you living, Jane?

349
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:33,640
我在问你呢
Not me. You.

350
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:36,870
你好像饱受身份困扰
You seem to be struggling with your identity.

351
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,430
希望这样说现任总统不会太...
If that's not too impertinent to say to a...

352
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:41,250
冒昧
sitting president.

353
00:22:43,950 --> 00:22:46,670
过来陪我换睡衣吧
Come keep me company while I put my jammies on.

354
00:22:54,490 --> 00:22:55,450
帮我一下
Please.

355
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:09,140
你在葬礼上佯装顺从
Your little show of compliance at the funeral

356
00:23:09,150 --> 00:23:13,280
却和维克多私下达成协议
as you made your side deal with Victor.

357
00:23:15,380 --> 00:23:16,640
让我不禁想
Makes me wonder.

358
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:19,960
现在呢
And now what?

359
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:22,430
你现在演的是哪一出
What do you call this show?

360
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:26,940
怎样在短短三周内让三亿两千三百万人都反对你
How to turn 323 million people against you in three short weeks?

361
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:29,160
恭喜  克莱尔
Congratulations, Claire.

362
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:31,980
你现在让所有人头疼
You've become a problem for everybody.

363
00:23:33,190 --> 00:23:34,130
还有
And...

364
00:23:35,420 --> 00:23:37,050
你要知道
Just so you know,

365
00:23:38,660 --> 00:23:40,620
叙利亚可能无可挽回了
Syria may be too far gone.

366
00:23:40,780 --> 00:23:42,360
告诉我该怎么办  简
Tell me what to do, Jane.

367
00:23:45,580 --> 00:23:47,530
我今晚参加了一个活动
I was at an event tonight.

368
00:23:48,150 --> 00:23:50,480
通常  总统都会参加
An event the president usually attends.

369
00:23:52,230 --> 00:23:53,800
今晚过得如何
And how was that evening?

370
00:23:56,580 --> 00:23:59,160
正在形成的风暴很难对付
The storm that's gathering is a rough one.

371
00:24:01,150 --> 00:24:02,770
你觉得他们什么时候会动手
When you think they'll strike?

372
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,050
我不知道
I have no idea.

373
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:14,100
有点晚了
It's late.

374
00:24:14,590 --> 00:24:16,170
我正是这意思
That's exactly what I'm saying.

375
00:24:21,290 --> 00:24:23,170
我想我该搬出去了
I think I should move out.

376
00:24:28,690 --> 00:24:29,750
我理解
I understand.

377
00:24:34,930 --> 00:24:37,500
你再这么下去  总统女士
Stick to this course, Madam President,

378
00:24:37,980 --> 00:24:38,950
那么...
and...

379
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:53,800
座无虚席呢
Full house.

380
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,930
你们想必是想听不同的答案
You must be looking for different answers

381
00:24:55,930 --> 00:24:58,100
这相同的问题已经问了...
to the same questions we've been going over for the last--

382
00:24:58,100 --> 00:24:59,120
24天
Now, 24 days.

383
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:01,300
而总统仍然没离开官邸
And the president still hasn't left the residence.

384
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:03,470
-我只能说...  -凯尔茜  拜托
- And this is where I say-- - Kelsey, come on.

385
00:25:06,050 --> 00:25:08,650
目前  与俄罗斯所达成的旨在维系
For now, the ground-breaking accord with Russia,

386
00:25:08,740 --> 00:25:11,530
叙利亚公正且持久的和平的突破性协议
which aims for a just and lasting peace in Syria,

387
00:25:11,540 --> 00:25:12,600
就足以说明一切
speaks for itself.

388
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,510
那么
So,

389
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,110
除非各位还有其他问题
unless there are any more questions,

390
00:25:15,110 --> 00:25:17,840
应该说新的问题  请说
or shall I say new questions? Yes.

391
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:20,660
真正操盘的人是不是副总统
Isn't the vice president really the one running the show,

392
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:22,880
实质上掌控了总统实权
essentially acting as president?

393
00:25:24,110 --> 00:25:26,500
有些内阁成员也这么说
There are members of the cabinet who are saying as much.

394
00:25:27,910 --> 00:25:30,710
首先  提及白宫事宜时
Well, firstly, I would refrain from using the word "show,"

395
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:32,600
不建议使用"操盘"这种字眼
when it comes to the White House.

396
00:25:33,330 --> 00:25:36,320
那么  今天就到此结束
And-- yeah. That's all for today.

397
00:25:36,490 --> 00:25:37,440
谢谢
Thank you.

398
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,270
你确定不饿吗
Are you sure you're not hungry?

399
00:25:45,810 --> 00:25:47,090
汤还不错
The soup is quite nice.

400
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,660
我不知道你怎么能...
I don't know how you can--

401
00:25:51,990 --> 00:25:52,960
吃得下吗
Eat?

402
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:56,690
不  我...
No, I'm...

403
00:25:57,370 --> 00:25:58,810
很高兴见你恢复食欲
glad to see you're eating.

404
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:04,110
总统女士  情势已经无法挽救
Madam President, it's beyond repair.

405
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:06,470
到了这个地步  你明白吧
You understand that, at this point?

406
00:26:08,620 --> 00:26:10,470
你失去了国会的支持
You've lost the Hill.

407
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:11,980
失去了内阁的支持
You've lost your cabinet.

408
00:26:13,190 --> 00:26:14,440
失去了国家的支持
You've lost the country.

409
00:26:16,970 --> 00:26:17,970
你输了
You've lost.

410
00:26:20,710 --> 00:26:23,340
你所属的政党也找不到理由支持你
Your own party can't even find a reason to support you.

411
00:26:23,470 --> 00:26:25,010
我恳求你
I entreat you--

412
00:26:25,010 --> 00:26:26,610
恳求我
You entreat me?

413
00:26:29,930 --> 00:26:30,970
辞职
Resign.

414
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:34,050
你这是以副总统的身份对我说吗
And are you speaking to me as vice president?

415
00:26:34,050 --> 00:26:36,060
我以一个人的身份对你说
I'm speaking to you as a person.

416
00:26:38,190 --> 00:26:39,210
就说是
Blame it on...

417
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:44,610
弗兰西斯的死带来的压力  总统职务的重荷
the strain after Francis' death, the strain of the office itself.

418
00:26:44,610 --> 00:26:48,770
说辞总是有  但你现在最好的结果
Language can be found, but the best you can hope for now...

419
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:52,610
就是带着尊严离开
is a dignified exit.

420
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:07,170
他最令人动容之处  在于他没法不如此
What's so moving about him is he can't help himself.

421
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:10,320
如此言行得体  充满人性
He can't help being decent. Human.

422
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,330
他那光荣的缺陷
His glorious flaw.

423
00:27:14,570 --> 00:27:16,210
这意味着
What this means is

424
00:27:16,730 --> 00:27:18,160
他们会行动的
they're gonna go through with it.

425
00:27:23,540 --> 00:27:24,540
不  马克
No, Mark.

426
00:27:25,610 --> 00:27:27,260
我哪也不去
I'm staying right where I am.

427
00:27:55,030 --> 00:27:56,390
给你两分钟
You got two minutes.

428
00:27:58,900 --> 00:28:01,270
{\pos(105.9,220)}圣达菲警局

429
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:04,000
这不是瑞秋·波斯纳
That's not Rachel Posner.

430
00:28:04,470 --> 00:28:05,400
是吗
Is it?

431
00:28:06,870 --> 00:28:08,350
你认识瑞秋·波斯纳
You knew Rachel Posner.

432
00:28:10,140 --> 00:28:11,090
应该
I mean...

433
00:28:11,670 --> 00:28:12,730
算是吧
yeah, I guess.

434
00:28:12,850 --> 00:28:14,970
你和她熟到可以把她名字给别人
Enough to use her name for someone else's ID?

435
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:15,940
这就是你做的生意吧
That's what you do, isn't it?

436
00:28:15,940 --> 00:28:17,450
给下位客户前一个人的名字
Kind of pay the names forward?

437
00:28:17,450 --> 00:28:18,330
不是
No.

438
00:28:18,330 --> 00:28:19,740
你给了瑞秋什么假名
What name did you give Rachel?

439
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:22,800
我不记得了
I don't remember.

440
00:28:23,290 --> 00:28:24,290
我说真的
I don't.

441
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:25,820
你最后一次见到她是什么时候
When did you last see her?

442
00:28:26,170 --> 00:28:27,080
饶了我吧
Come on.

443
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:30,040
可能几年前吧
Couple of years ago or something.

444
00:28:30,690 --> 00:28:31,990
在她上班的地方
It was where she worked.

445
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:33,320
她死了吗
Is she dead?

446
00:28:36,990 --> 00:28:39,500
-跟我没关系  -你是不是帮凶
- I got nothing to do with that. - Did you help kill her?

447
00:28:40,990 --> 00:28:42,140
我在跟你说话
I'm talking to you.

448
00:28:46,330 --> 00:28:48,470
别这样  我要找律师
Man. I want my lawyer.

449
00:28:49,780 --> 00:28:50,750
你认识
Do you know...

450
00:28:51,420 --> 00:28:52,550
道格·斯坦普吗
Doug Stamper?

451
00:28:53,260 --> 00:28:54,170
不认识
No.

452
00:28:54,790 --> 00:28:55,980
你给了她什么假名
What name did you give her?

453
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:57,800
她叫什么名字
What was her name?

454
00:28:58,660 --> 00:28:59,610
丽莎
Lisa.

455
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:02,050
-丽莎  -嗯  丽莎  凯茜
- Lisa? - Yeah. Lisa Cassie.

456
00:29:02,050 --> 00:29:03,560
-丽莎·凯茜  -凯茜  丽莎
- Lisa Cassie? - Cassie, Lisa.

457
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:05,360
-对  -丽莎和凯茜
- Yeah. - Lisa and Cassie?

458
00:29:47,980 --> 00:29:49,420
你回到白宫了
Back at the White House.

459
00:29:51,070 --> 00:29:52,220
你住进了他的房间
You took his room.

460
00:29:54,490 --> 00:29:55,510
更宽敞些
It's bigger.

461
00:29:59,260 --> 00:30:00,140
你能告诉我为什么
Can you tell me why

462
00:30:00,140 --> 00:30:03,270
我们非要现在在这里见面吗
it was so important that we meet here and now?

463
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:06,180
老实说  我是希望能在白宫西楼会面的
Honestly, I was hoping we could meet in the West Wing.

464
00:30:06,810 --> 00:30:08,820
我已经在这里足不出户...
I haven't left the residence in...

465
00:30:09,670 --> 00:30:11,710
我相信你还是看新闻的
Well, I'm sure you still read the news.

466
00:30:13,610 --> 00:30:14,790
而且你的赦免
And your pardon...

467
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:17,820
没有帮到我或弗兰西斯
hasn't helped me or Francis.

468
00:30:19,100 --> 00:30:20,670
我在这里感觉不舒服
I don't feel comfortable here.

469
00:30:24,210 --> 00:30:27,290
不管你在这里有什么不好的回忆  道格
Whatever bad memories you may have, Doug...

470
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:31,490
有时候要花很长时间才能理解
sometimes it takes a long time to understand

471
00:30:31,490 --> 00:30:33,750
是谁真正伤害了我们
who's the real source of our harm.

472
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:37,340
我没能让你相信我
And I have failed to make you trust me,

473
00:30:38,290 --> 00:30:39,410
这太遗憾了
and that's a shame.

474
00:30:47,170 --> 00:30:48,480
我相信我所了解的
I trust what I know.

475
00:30:51,260 --> 00:30:53,410
你有很多敌人  他们低估了你
You have enemies, and they underestimate you.

476
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,800
你认为他们会怎样攻击我
And how do you think they'll come at me?

477
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:59,170
科尔议员对你说什么了吗
Has Congressman Cole said anything to you?

478
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,490
我觉得她还活着
I think she's alive.

479
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:03,870
凯茜·杜兰特
Cathy Durant.

480
00:31:04,700 --> 00:31:06,930
我不知道她在哪里或在搞什么事  但是...
I don't know where she is or what she's up to, but...

481
00:31:07,870 --> 00:31:09,160
我知道你会想知道的
I knew you'd want to know.

482
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:18,180
我想让你知道一件事情
I want you to know something.

483
00:31:20,790 --> 00:31:22,480
弗兰西斯死在这间屋子里
Francis died in this room.

484
00:31:22,990 --> 00:31:25,520
我告诉大家他死在我床上
I told everyone it was in my bed.

485
00:31:27,030 --> 00:31:29,840
但其实就在这片地板上
But it was right there on the floor.

486
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:31,580
不管是谁杀了他
Whoever killed him.

487
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:38,970
我遗漏了什么吗
Am I missing something?

488
00:31:40,580 --> 00:31:41,850
杀了他的人
Whoever killed him

489
00:31:42,250 --> 00:31:45,220
将得到她或他应有的下场
will get what she or he deserves.

490
00:31:55,300 --> 00:31:57,950
时机决定了宇宙的形状
Timing decided the shape of the universe.

491
00:31:58,540 --> 00:31:59,560
谁说的
Who said that?

492
00:31:59,670 --> 00:32:00,590
我
Me.

493
00:32:01,870 --> 00:32:04,140
地狱是明白得太晚的真理
Hell is truth seen too late.

494
00:32:05,750 --> 00:32:06,780
这是你说的吗
Did you say that?

495
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:08,610
托马斯·霍布斯
Thomas Hobbes.

496
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,140
厄舍
Usher...

497
00:32:12,380 --> 00:32:13,360
你下注
your bet.

498
00:32:15,540 --> 00:32:17,810
-我要看牌  谢谢  -别这么礼貌
- I'll check, please. - Don't be polite.

499
00:32:17,810 --> 00:32:19,290
我以前和你玩过
I played with you before.

500
00:32:19,630 --> 00:32:20,870
我知道你有好牌
I know you're holding.

501
00:32:21,090 --> 00:32:22,130
比尔  你确定吗
Bill, you sure?

502
00:32:22,130 --> 00:32:24,020
我可以在下一手分牌给你
I can deal you in on the next hand.

503
00:32:24,750 --> 00:32:27,530
-我不玩  -她真疯了吗
- I don't play. - Is it true she's a basket case?

504
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:30,160
或者就是一个普通的民主党人
Or just a plain old Democrat.

505
00:32:31,100 --> 00:32:32,510
我会把信准备好
So, I'll have the letter.

506
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:34,300
要看我的牌得再加一百
That's a hundred to see mine.

507
00:32:34,300 --> 00:32:35,850
等时间到了  汉克
And when it comes time, Hank,

508
00:32:36,190 --> 00:32:36,960
我不想最后
I don't want to end up

509
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:39,460
在参议院里  一手拿着一张纸
on the Senate floor with a piece of paper in one hand--

510
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:40,960
另一只手上只有你的蛋
And your balls in the other?

511
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:42,640
我们都是过来人
We've all been there.

512
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,190
别说我的蛋了
Just keep my balls out of it.

513
00:32:44,350 --> 00:32:46,180
厄舍  你要让我去拉票
Usher, you want me to whip,

514
00:32:46,190 --> 00:32:49,130
却不让我告诉参议员们他们在为什么投票
but you don't want me to tell my senators what they're voting on.

515
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:51,300
还要不经过讨论就通过
And pass without debate.

516
00:32:51,300 --> 00:32:52,230
我不跟
I'm out.

517
00:32:52,990 --> 00:32:54,750
至少告诉我他们会得到什么
At least tell me what they're getting.

518
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:58,540
白宫的新主人
A new resident in the White House.

519
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:06,240
总统先生
Well, Mr. President.

520
00:33:07,050 --> 00:33:08,960
你是跟还是不跟
Are you in or are you out?

521
00:33:12,330 --> 00:33:13,280
我跟
I call.

522
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:15,820
还有...
And...

523
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:19,500
加注500
bump you 500.

524
00:33:24,570 --> 00:33:27,140
我永远不会称这里为敌方领地
I would never call this enemy territory.

525
00:33:28,430 --> 00:33:29,760
听起来可能有点奇怪
It might sound quaint,

526
00:33:30,450 --> 00:33:32,170
但我相信共和制
but I believe in the Republic.

527
00:33:32,570 --> 00:33:34,400
感谢你的到来
Well, thank you for coming.

528
00:33:38,060 --> 00:33:39,600
这种媒体的攻击
It's not sustainable.

529
00:33:40,020 --> 00:33:41,900
是持续不下去的
This media onslaught.

530
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:45,930
不知你是否可以考虑叫你的狗收手
I wonder if you'd consider calling off the dogs.

531
00:33:46,910 --> 00:33:49,730
就暂缓一下  几天就行
All I'm asking for is a pause. Couple of days or so.

532
00:33:50,530 --> 00:33:52,920
你恭维我了  总统女士
You flatter me, Madam President.

533
00:33:52,930 --> 00:33:55,100
但我的能力也不过如此
But my reach only goes so far.

534
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:56,930
看来他们想让你辞职
It seems they want you to resign.

535
00:33:57,530 --> 00:33:58,610
是谁想
Who's they?

536
00:33:58,610 --> 00:33:59,580
谁不想
Who isn't?

537
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,160
请原谅我的直言不讳
Pardon my bluntness.

538
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,840
不  我喜欢直言不讳  这样节省时间
Oh, no, I enjoy bluntness. Saves time.

539
00:34:04,070 --> 00:34:07,260
但我是否应该因身为女性而辞职
But should I resign for the high crime of being a female?

540
00:34:07,260 --> 00:34:09,680
我认为有比那更深刻的原因
Oh, I think the reasoning goes deeper than that.

541
00:34:10,050 --> 00:34:11,370
我认为...
I think...

542
00:34:12,230 --> 00:34:14,700
这只是我个人的观点
and this is just my perspective,

543
00:34:15,010 --> 00:34:16,890
-如果你想听的话  -请尽管说
- if you want to hear it. - Oh, please.

544
00:34:18,140 --> 00:34:20,350
我们家族与你之间的争斗
Dueling agendas between my family,

545
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:24,380
已经开始自行发展了
and, well, you, have taken on their own life.

546
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:28,610
从某种意义上说  你丈夫又不肯放过你
And in some sense, your husband just won't leave you alone,

547
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,310
是吧
will he?

548
00:34:33,750 --> 00:34:35,520
我无法改变过去
I can't change history.

549
00:34:35,720 --> 00:34:37,390
不过有时候你肯定希望自己能
I'll bet sometimes you'd like to.

550
00:34:39,270 --> 00:34:40,960
你不想抹掉他吗
Wouldn't you like to erase him?

551
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,130
总统女士
Madam President...

552
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:46,320
你已故的丈夫跟我妈妈说了许多事
your dead husband told my mother things.

553
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,440
你不想让全世界知道的事
Things you don't want the world to know.

554
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:52,500
我觉得  一个死人的话没什么用
A dead man's words are worthless as far as I'm concerned.

555
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:54,910
要是他所说的能被证实就不一样了
Not when his claims can be verified.

556
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:02,520
不过有办法让关于某个人的记忆消失
It's possible to make the memory of a person disappear.

557
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:04,820
用数字手段
Digitally.

558
00:35:05,790 --> 00:35:08,170
至少能把记忆移得远远的
