- Madam President, I-- - I know. It's fine.

740
00:46:15,530 --> 00:46:18,010
说你俩当时在约会
You just say you were dating.

741
00:46:18,910 --> 00:46:20,010
在谈恋爱
You were in love.

742
00:46:20,770 --> 00:46:22,240
有次在私下里
And in a private moment,

743
00:46:23,700 --> 00:46:26,810
他向你透露了他怀疑
he told you about his suspicions regarding

744
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:29,910
马克·厄舍与俄罗斯串谋
Mark Usher and his collusion with Russia.

745
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:33,070
而你最后一次见到他时
And the last time you saw him,

746
00:46:33,070 --> 00:46:35,060
他正要去副总统的宅邸
he was on his way to the vice president's home

747
00:46:35,060 --> 00:46:36,180
与他对峙
to confront him.

748
00:46:39,180 --> 00:46:41,780
我不会让副总统逍遥法外的
I'm not going to let the vice president get away with this.

749
00:46:43,660 --> 00:46:45,900
你和我身为女人
You and I, as women,

750
00:46:47,070 --> 00:46:48,760
我们必须反击
we have to fight back.

751
00:46:49,260 --> 00:46:51,020
我需要你和我并肩作战
I need you by my side.

752
00:46:58,890 --> 00:47:00,760
在我们送出信之前
And before we transmit the letter,

753
00:47:01,500 --> 00:47:04,310
我想请所有人低下头
I'd like to suggest we all take a moment to bow our heads

754
00:47:05,250 --> 00:47:06,920
为我们伟大的祖国祈祷
and pray for this great nation.

755
00:47:28,760 --> 00:47:30,240
能把信递给我吗
Could you pass me that letter?

756
00:47:47,630 --> 00:47:49,620
还有  把你们的东西收好
And gather all of your things.

757
00:47:49,850 --> 00:47:52,470
在场所有内阁成员
Every single cabinet member in this room

758
00:47:52,620 --> 00:47:53,840
都可以走了
is dismissed.

759
00:47:54,300 --> 00:47:55,670
你们都被解雇了
You're all fired.

760
00:47:57,150 --> 00:47:58,260
送他们出去
Escort them out.

761
00:48:06,530 --> 00:48:07,490
你知道
You know,

762
00:48:08,120 --> 00:48:09,740
我从没想过你是
I never took you for someone

763
00:48:09,740 --> 00:48:11,980
想入主白宫的人
who wanted to get himself into the Oval.

764
00:48:12,410 --> 00:48:15,930
不过是个四年的饭碗  幸运的话是八年
All it is, is a four year job, eight if you're lucky.

765
00:48:18,690 --> 00:48:19,630
你在哪
Where are you?

766
00:48:20,810 --> 00:48:21,740
什么
What?

767
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:24,790
好  我马上回来
All right. I'm on my way back.

768
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:28,730
要是她干预签署  那就是妨碍司法
Listen, if she prevented the signing, that's obstruction.

769
00:48:28,900 --> 00:48:30,780
可能会使她遭弹劾
And likely, it's impeachable.

770
00:48:30,780 --> 00:48:31,720
听见了吗
You hear me?

771
00:48:32,620 --> 00:48:34,000
细节仍在传来
Details are still coming in.

772
00:48:34,010 --> 00:48:37,410
但是据了解  今天联调局
But we're being told there are reports that the FBI...

773
00:48:37,410 --> 00:48:39,710
-马克  -收到证据显示
- Mark. - ...has today been provided evidence...

774
00:48:39,710 --> 00:48:41,830
-去看电视  -马克·厄舍与俄国官员
- Get to a television. - ...that Mark Usher had quote...

775
00:48:41,830 --> 00:48:44,230
-或是电脑  -有"情节重大
- Or a computer. - ..."significant and ongoing...

776
00:48:43,240 --> 00:48:48,100
联调局调查副总统与俄罗斯勾结的指控

777
00:48:44,230 --> 00:48:45,120
或是打开电台
Or a goddamn radio.

778
00:48:45,120 --> 00:48:48,420
且仍在持续的私下联系"
...contact outside the logs with Russian officials."

779
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:51,000
这促成了总统近期所签署的
This leading up to and during the president's

780
00:48:51,010 --> 00:48:53,750
反应两极化的叙利亚和平协议
recent polarizing Syrian peace deal.

781
00:48:53,830 --> 00:48:56,210
联调局会调查此事
The FBI's expected to look into the matter,

782
00:48:56,210 --> 00:48:59,180
但他们尚未宣布是否会启动
but has yet to announce whether or not they are opening

783
00:48:59,220 --> 00:49:01,080
正式调查
an official investigation.

784
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:04,720
如果属实  这将是本届多灾多难的政府
If so, this could be a catastrophic setback

785
00:49:04,720 --> 00:49:07,360
遭遇的又一灾难性挫败
for an already-beleaguered administration.

786
00:49:07,530 --> 00:49:12,050
在我们开始之前  我想给你一个请辞的机会
Before we begin, I'd like to offer you the chance to resign.

787
00:49:17,150 --> 00:49:18,410
那我就不打扰你了
I'll leave you to it then.

788
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:26,040
我和俄罗斯从没有过非正式联系  从来没有
I never had any contact with any Russians outside the logs. None.

789
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:29,450
1991年夏天你曾在副外交部长左尔金位于
You vacationed at Deputy Foreign Minister Zorkin's family dacha

790
00:49:29,450 --> 00:49:31,790
-黑海的乡间别墅度假  -二十年前的事了
- on the Black Sea in summer 1991. - That was 20 years ago.

791
00:49:31,790 --> 00:49:33,640
我们回溯一下  从凯尔茜·斯图尔特小姐的证词
Let's work backwards, start with questions that have arisen

792
00:49:33,640 --> 00:49:35,760
引起的疑问开始
after Ms. Kelsey Stewart's deposition.

793
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:36,770
谁
Who?

794
00:49:38,210 --> 00:49:41,380
我们定位她的手机在贝尔波特的一家酒水店
We located her phone in a liquor store in Bellport.

795
00:49:41,630 --> 00:49:42,930
她知道应用的事了
She knows about the app.

796
00:49:43,790 --> 00:49:45,080
应该是吧
We should assume so.

797
00:49:45,540 --> 00:49:46,970
你告诉我舅舅了吗
Have you told my uncle yet?

798
00:49:47,300 --> 00:49:48,320
我联系不上他
I can't reach him.

799
00:49:49,150 --> 00:49:50,870
我也联系不上你母亲
I can't reach your mother, either.

800
00:49:50,920 --> 00:49:52,540
我们已经派人追踪那位记者
We have some men tracking the journalist.

801
00:49:52,540 --> 00:49:54,810
我们还不知道她是否取得了任何证据
But we don't even know if she has her hands on anything yet.

802
00:49:56,010 --> 00:49:58,640
-谢泼德先生的包裹  -谢谢
- Package for Mr. Shepherd. - Oh, thank you.

803
00:50:02,170 --> 00:50:03,480
写着是给你的
This is addressed to you.

804
00:50:15,030 --> 00:50:16,370
请让我独处一会儿
Leave me alone, please.

805
00:50:28,900 --> 00:50:30,750
我是凯瑟琳·杜兰特
My name is Catherine Durant.

806
00:50:31,150 --> 00:50:35,570
今天是2017年7月18日  星期二
Today is Tuesday, July 18, 2017.

807
00:50:35,820 --> 00:50:37,090
时间是
And the time... 

808
00:50:38,030 --> 00:50:40,020
晚上8点37分
8:37 p.m.

809
00:50:40,870 --> 00:50:43,580
在我开始之前  我想说
Now, before I begin, let me just say...

810
00:50:45,010 --> 00:50:47,050
历史必将带给
that every punishment

811
00:50:47,450 --> 00:50:51,730
克莱尔·安德伍德的所有惩罚
that history will surely visit upon Claire Underwood

812
00:50:52,450 --> 00:50:55,370
都是她罪有应得
will be exactly what she deserves.

813
00:50:55,580 --> 00:50:59,590
我万分懊悔当初接受了她丈夫提供的
I rue the day that I accepted her husband's offer

814
00:50:59,860 --> 00:51:01,800
国务卿一职
of secretary of state.

815
00:51:02,210 --> 00:51:03,200
好了
Now, then...

816
00:51:04,730 --> 00:51:09,730
我发誓我接下来绝无虚言
I hereby swear that everything I'm about to say is the truth.

817
00:51:10,740 --> 00:51:13,550
她丈夫六小时前失踪了
Her husband has disappeared, as of six hours ago.

818
00:51:14,100 --> 00:51:16,160
-你还想听吗  -不了
- Do you want to hear any more? - No.

819
00:51:16,320 --> 00:51:17,460
我知道后面是什么
I know the rest.

820
00:51:20,500 --> 00:51:22,040
你觉得是俄罗斯人帮他们逃掉的吗
Do you think the Russians got them out?

821
00:51:23,040 --> 00:51:25,620
不  我能肯定是
Uh, no, I'm sure of it.

822
00:51:26,720 --> 00:51:28,730
你觉得她发给其他人了吗
Do you think she sent it to anyone else?

823
00:51:28,730 --> 00:51:30,370
发了我们早就知道了
We would know about it by now.

824
00:51:31,070 --> 00:51:33,400
我让纳森候命于你
I've asked Nathan to be available to you.

825
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:36,480
我知道你俩合作很默契
I know how well you two work with one another.

826
00:51:37,390 --> 00:51:38,380
我们会找到她的
We'll find her.

827
00:51:40,530 --> 00:51:41,590
道格  我还没忘
And, Doug, I haven't forgotten

828
00:51:41,590 --> 00:51:43,880
我们对彼此的承诺
about the promise we made to each other.

829
00:51:44,020 --> 00:51:45,320
但愿你也没有
I hope you haven't.

830
00:52:19,540 --> 00:52:21,310
我刚从新墨西哥州回来
I just got back from New Mexico.

831
00:52:21,910 --> 00:52:24,820
你把瑞秋怎么了  还是把凯茜怎么了
What did you do with Rachel? Or is it Cassie?

832
00:52:26,740 --> 00:52:28,100
我离你只有五分钟路程
I'm five minutes away.

833
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:29,460
挂了电话
Hang up the phone.

834
00:52:29,620 --> 00:52:30,910
-道格  -挂掉
- Doug-- - Hang it up

835
00:52:30,910 --> 00:52:32,520
不然我再不会联系你
or you'll never hear from me again.

836
00:52:33,290 --> 00:52:34,420
我去找你
I'll come to you.

837
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:48,360
纳森
Nathan,

838
00:52:48,710 --> 00:52:49,980
你还在听吗
are you still listening?

839
00:52:52,110 --> 00:52:54,110
你相信她会保护你就太傻了
You're a fool to think she'll protect you.

840
00:53:03,430 --> 00:53:06,640
这似乎挺合适  我回来工作后
Seems fitting, somehow, that you're the first

841
00:53:06,640 --> 00:53:09,770
第一个见的人就是你
person I meet with after I've returned to work.

842
00:53:10,580 --> 00:53:12,900
真是好轮回啊
There's something very full circle about it.

843
00:53:13,620 --> 00:53:15,620
你跟你儿子谈过咯
So, you've talked to your son.

844
00:53:15,830 --> 00:53:18,470
准确说那不是你儿子
Or rather, not your son.

845
00:53:19,860 --> 00:53:23,170
你知道那时候胎儿有多大了吗
Do you know how developed a fetus is by then?

846
00:53:23,570 --> 00:53:25,740
16周
Sixteen weeks is...

847
00:53:26,290 --> 00:53:27,760
那可是成型的胎儿
beyond the beyond.

848
00:53:32,570 --> 00:53:34,950
16周的胎儿有这么大了
That is what 16 weeks looks like.

849
00:53:35,020 --> 00:53:37,220
这画面在我脑海中挥之不去
That is what I can't get out of my head.

850
00:53:38,030 --> 00:53:40,490
我在学梅乐蒂·科鲁兹说话呢
I'm quoting Melody Cruz here, by the way.

851
00:53:40,820 --> 00:53:43,240
她刚录好视频  明天就放
She just taped her segment, due to run tomorrow.

852
00:53:44,200 --> 00:53:46,070
还有道具增强表现力
Visual aids and everything.

853
00:53:47,130 --> 00:53:49,820
美国人民会首次听到
For the first time ever, Americans will hear the story

854
00:53:49,820 --> 00:53:51,540
膝下无子的总统
of a childless president...

855
00:53:52,370 --> 00:53:53,650
在婚后
who had an abortion,

856
00:53:54,230 --> 00:53:55,330
做了流产
while married,

857
00:53:55,930 --> 00:53:57,610
打掉了16周的胎儿
at 16 weeks.

858
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:00,600
我就想看看你的表情
I wanted to see your face.

859
00:54:00,960 --> 00:54:03,520
我想看你意识到弗兰克的背叛
I wanted to see Frank's betrayal register.

860
00:54:04,320 --> 00:54:06,930
现在谁都管不住自己的嘴
Nobody can keep their mouths shut these days.

861
00:54:07,250 --> 00:54:09,260
秘密都带进坟墓了还能被挖出来
Not even to-the-death secrets are safe.

862
00:54:09,260 --> 00:54:10,380
真可耻
It's shameful.

863
00:54:12,190 --> 00:54:13,730
但说实话  哪样更痛苦
But honestly, what's worse?

864
00:54:14,090 --> 00:54:15,600
他泄露了你的秘密
That he betrayed your secret

865
00:54:16,030 --> 00:54:18,380
还是你等到16周才堕胎
or that you waited until 16 weeks?

866
00:54:18,380 --> 00:54:20,200
你和你的党派
You and your party.

867
00:54:20,350 --> 00:54:23,350
就一副道貌岸然的样子  
Your moral rectitude, how convenient.

868
00:54:23,380 --> 00:54:25,840
你自己的话你一个字也不信  安奈特
You don't even believe half of what you say, Annette.

869
00:54:26,660 --> 00:54:27,600
放吧
Run it.

870
00:54:28,040 --> 00:54:29,170
科鲁兹的报道
Cruz's piece.

871
00:54:29,680 --> 00:54:30,610
放吧
Run it.

872
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:33,520
然后回去
And then go home

873
00:54:34,050 --> 00:54:36,560
跟邓肯说说他怎么来的
and talk to Duncan about the beginning of life.

874
00:54:38,260 --> 00:54:39,990
你走之前
But actually before you go,

875
00:54:40,240 --> 00:54:42,300
我想给你看样东西  来
I want to show you something. Come with me.

876
00:54:59,700 --> 00:55:01,730
见过我的新内阁
Meet my new cabinet.

877
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:06,520
我就想看看你的表情
I just wanted to see your face.

878
00:55:16,720 --> 00:55:19,900
谢谢大家临危受命
Thank you all for assembling at such short notice.

879
00:55:21,170 --> 00:55:25,420
我想感谢各位的奉献精神
And I want to thank you for your willingness to serve.

880
00:55:26,880 --> 00:55:30,440
我很期待能共同建立一个新美国
I am looking forward to building a new America together

881
00:55:31,110 --> 00:55:33,540
我们就从今天开始
and our work begins today.

882
00:55:35,260 --> 00:55:36,510
现在  请你们
Now, if you could all

883
00:55:36,790 --> 00:55:40,620
将左手放在自己面前的《宪法》上
place your left hand on the Constitution in front of you.

884
00:55:41,950 --> 00:55:43,520
跟我念
And repeat after me:

885
00:55:43,860 --> 00:55:46,340
本人庄严宣誓
I do solemnly swear

886
00:55:47,330 --> 00:55:49,300
下手绝不留情
to take no prisoners.

887
00:55:50,400 --> 00:56:00,400
{\an5}{\pos(193,147)}今年6月第一夫人梅兰妮因肾病紧急入院做了手术
根据病情判断  媒体以为术后三五天她就会重回公众视野
但是没想到梅兰妮一直玩失踪  长达25天没在媒体前露面
第一夫人玩失踪引发媒体各种猜测  有的说她乘机整容
有的说她跟老公特朗普闹翻离宫出走...
不过25天后  她再次出现在公共场合  所有谣言都不攻自破
不过白宫也一直没有解释为什么第一夫人需要这么长时间闭门养病

888
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:30,400
{\an5}{\pos(193,147)}宪法第25修正案主要规定当总统和副总统职位出现空缺时
应怎样启动继任程序  历史上因总统副总统辞职
总统体检麻醉等原因  共启用过六次
本集中由副总统和内阁启动继任程序的第四条款  历史上从未被使用过
特朗普上任后  他的政敌和媒体
一直对他的施政能力和各种言论进行猛烈攻击
一些人曾在电视访谈中称特朗普性情乖张  像疯了一样
精神状态不适合履行总统职务  应该启动第25修正案

889
00:57:00,400 --> 00:57:10,400
{\an5}{\pos(193,147)}18年9月21日  《纽约时报》爆料称  司法部副部长罗森斯坦
曾私下建议启用第25修正案  把特朗普从总统位置上赶下来
并表示自己可以暗中配戴窃听装置进入总统办公室
偷录特朗普讲话  以证明总统无法控制白宫局势
罗森斯坦本人坚决否认《纽约时报》的报道
但据说特朗普看了报道后一度想要炒掉罗森斯坦  但是后来回转心意
在空军一号上同罗森斯坦面对面交谈后  决定不去动他
罗森斯坦是负责通俄门调查的最高级官员
如果特朗普把他炒掉  可能会引发"总统干预司法"的危机

